, 12, and 13 years old. Tobacco shed of American Sumatra Tobacco Co. In these two sheds were 41 girls and boys from 10 to 15 years, and only 24 girls and women of 16 years and up. The leaf-boys get $1.50 a day and some of the stringers of 10 and 12 make $1.20 a day, according to the Supt.  Location: S[outh] Windsor, Connecticut", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2018678625/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/nclc/item/2018678626/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/nclc.00704", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2018678626/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2018678626/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/nclc.00704/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2018678626"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["hine, lewis wickes"], "date": "1917-01-01", "dates": ["1917"], "description": ["1 photographic print."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2021-09-01T22:53:56.861Z", "group": ["nclc", "catalog-split-14", "catalog", "national-child-labor-committee", "main-catalog-split-14", "main-catalog"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2018678626/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/nclc/00700/00704_150px.jpg#h=108&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/nclc/00700/00704t.gif#h=108&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/nclc/00700/00704r.jpg#h=461&w=640", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/nclc/00700/00704v.jpg#h=738&w=1024"], "index": 8, "language": ["english"], "location": ["south windsor", "connecticut", "united states"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/jpg", "image/tif"], "number": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/ncl2004005019/pp", "http://www.loc.gov/item/20689587", "2018678626", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2018678626", "2018-11-02t15:47:02"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["photo, print, drawing"], "partof": ["prints & photographs online catalog (library of congress)", "catalog", "prints and photographs division", "national child labor committee